== The Turba Philosophorum (The Assembly of the Sages)

#hm-note[
  The Turba is one of the earliest and most important Latin alchemical texts. It is presented as a transcript of a gathering of pre-Socratic philosophers (Anaximander, Anaximenes, etc.) discussing the nature of the Prime Matter. It establishes the "Monad" as the source of all elements.
]

=== The Unity of Matter
- *The Chaos:* The sages agree that all things arise from a single, chaotic substance that contains all possibilities.
- *Transmutation:* Because all elements (Fire, Air, Water, Earth) are merely different "weights" or "qualities" of the same underlying matter, they can be changed into one another.

=== The Four Elements
#doctrine[
  "The air is the thinness of the fire, the water is the thickness of the air, and the earth is the thickness of the water."
]
- The Turba emphasizes that the elements are not separate "things" but states of density and heat.

=== The Key Operations (Coded)
- *The Egg:* The philosophical vessel is often compared to an egg, containing the yolk (Sulfur), the white (Mercury), and the shell (Salt).
- *The Cooking:* Constant, gentle heat is the secret to maturing the matter. "Cook, and cook again, and do not be weary."
- *The Colors:* The text mentions the transition from Black (Nigredo) to White (Albedo) as the primary sign of success.

=== TTAO Core Lesson
- *The Assembly:* The student should view the different "voices" in the Turba not as literal people, but as different aspects of the mind debating the nature of reality until they reach a unified "Conjunction."
